explanation: The solution uses a stack to process the string. When encountering an opening parenthesis, it pushes it onto the stack. When encountering a closing parenthesis, it pops elements from the stack until it finds the matching opening parenthesis, reverses the popped elements, and pushes them back onto the stack. Finally, it joins the stack into a string and returns it. This approach efficiently reverses the substrings within parentheses.

